        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(media-understanding): align video base64 byte limits",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nVideo max byte limits are compared after estimating the inline base64 payload size, but `resolveVideoMaxBase64Bytes()` converted the configured raw byte limit with `Math.floor(maxBytes * (4 / 3))`. That underestimates any raw byte limit that is not divisible by 3, so a video exactly within the configured raw byte cap can be rejected before provider submission.\n\nFor example, `maxBytes = 1` expands to a 4-byte base64 payload, but the previous resolved cap was 1.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe helper already has the correct base64 sizing primitive, `estimateBase64Size(bytes)`, which rounds byte counts to complete base64 quanta with `Math.ceil(bytes / 3) * 4`. This change reuses that primitive for the configured max byte limit, keeping the comparison symmetric with the per-file estimate while preserving the shared `DEFAULT_VIDEO_MAX_BASE64_BYTES` cap.\n\nA focused regression test covers the non-multiple-of-three boundaries that previously failed.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers with custom video byte limits no longer see valid videos rejected only because the expanded base64 limit was rounded down. The global payload cap still applies, so this does not relax the existing maximum request size guard.\n\n## Evidence\n\nDirect boundary probe:\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx -e \"import('./packages/media-understanding-common/src/video.ts').then(({ resolveVideoMaxBase64Bytes }) => console.log(JSON.stringify([1, 2, 3, 4].map((maxBytes) => ({ maxBytes, maxBase64Bytes: resolveVideoMaxBase64Bytes(maxBytes) })))))\"\n[{\"maxBytes\":1,\"maxBase64Bytes\":4},{\"maxBytes\":2,\"maxBase64Bytes\":4},{\"maxBytes\":3,\"maxBase64Bytes\":4},{\"maxBytes\":4,\"maxBase64Bytes\":8}]\n```\n\nTargeted unit test:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit.config.ts packages/media-understanding-common/src/video.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 C:/Users/lin20/Documents/New project 3/openclaw\n\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  3 passed (3)\n   Start at  21:04:15\n   Duration  967ms (transform 682ms, setup 515ms, import 16ms, tests 145ms, environment 0ms)\n```\n\nFormatting:\n\n```text\n$ node_modules\\.bin\\oxfmt.cmd --check packages/media-understanding-common/src/video.ts packages/media-understanding-common/src/video.test.ts\nChecking formatting...\n\nAll matched files use the correct format.\nFinished in 1235ms on 2 files using 32 threads.\n```\n\nWhitespace:\n\n```text\n$ git diff --check\n```\n\n## AI-assisted\n\nPrepared with Codex. I reviewed the change, understand the touched code path, and kept the PR focused on the bug described above.\n",
